rComments: Schimdt is a good teacher. She remarkably understands what she is teaching. The class is not so hard (3 exams+ 1 paper). Don't forget to get the past exams! 90% of questions in the exam are just the same as the past exams!!!
Supa dupa easy class.  Yet it sucked going three times a week...in lincoln theater(P.O.S. lecture hall)
This course is supposed to be an easy A, but there is tons to memorize.

easy if you go to lecture and actually pay attention. minimal work...mostly just taking notes (which are online) and studying (which doesnt really help for the tests).  ok for a gen ed...easy A if work is put into it.

In order to do well in this class, you have to understand one very important thing: half the class has a copy of last semester's upcoming exam, which reflects almost perfectly what this semester's exam will be. Too bad for those who study hard.
Supposed to be an easy class, but requires a lot of math and chemistry and tons of memorizing. Schmidt is a good teacher though and answers a lot of questions during class.
Pretty easy class, very large, its ok for a gen ed, but not the greatest
